Top Stories (February 7)

DUKE ENERGY TO BUILD 6,000 MW OF NEW POWER CAPACITY
Duke Energy Corp.'s North American unit will build more than 6,000 megawatts 
of new power generation capacity in time for summer 2002 demand.
