CALPINE CONFIRMS $4.6B, 10-YEAR CALIFORNIA POWER SALES PACT
Calpine Corp. confirmed that it has received a 10-year power sales agreement 
valued at $4.6 billion from the state of California.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/07/eng-djn/eng-djn_124054_236_361002186313

US FERC UPHOLDS PROGRESS ENERGY MERGER IN RTO CHALLENGES
The U.S. Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Wednesday rejected challenges 
to its approval of the Progress Energy (PGN) merger.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/07/eng-djn/eng-djn_152059_123_842589142732

BUSH FACES POWER STRUGGLE IN DEVISING NATIONAL ENERGY PLAN
Not even a week into office, President Bush was faced with a possible 
domestic crisis: power outages, shortages and utility bankruptcies in the 
nation's most populous, financially powerful state.
